The paper focuses on deep learning with Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for image-based classification and enhancement, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach for feature representation that is conducive for CNN-based deep learning, which suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of minimization of pairwise distances similar to multi-dimensional scaling, which suggests that it may belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the proposed framework to biological datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
